        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nUpdates `npm-shrinkwrap.json` to resolve `hono@4.12.18` to `hono@4.12.23`, addressing 4 moderate security vulnerabilities reported in issue #91301.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- Updated `node_modules/hono` from `4.12.18` to `4.12.23` in `npm-shrinkwrap.json`\r\n\r\n## Security advisories fixed\r\n\r\n- GHSA-xrhx-7g5j-rcj5\r\n- GHSA-3hrh-pfw6-9m5x\r\n- GHSA-f577-qrjj-4474\r\n- GHSA-2gCR-mfcq-wcc3\r\n\r\nAll advisories list first patched version as `4.12.21`; this PR updates to `4.12.23` (latest available).\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `npm-shrinkwrap.json` updated with correct integrity hash for `hono@4.12.23`\r\n- Dependency range `^4.11.4` from `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk@1.29.0` satisfied by `4.12.23`\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\nN/A - This is a dependency version update that will be verified by downstream `npm audit` runs. The fix is straightforward:\r\n- Before: `hono@4.12.18` (vulnerable)\r\n- After: `hono@4.12.23` (patched)\r\n\r\njust the patched version, it is safe\r\n<img width=\"1334\" height=\"733\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2b5c3980-b83e-4047-b10e-33c2d8e26835\" />\r\n\r\n\r\nDownstream users can verify by running `npm audit` after installing this version of OpenClaw.\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [x] `npm-shrinkwrap.json` updated with correct version and integrity hash\r\n- [ ] Downstream `npm audit` passes (requires publish/install)\r\n",
